Not impressed. I tried some chicken tacos and some pork tacos. The pork was EXTREMELY fatty, like more than half my taco meat was fat. On the chicken, I hit a really big, weird chunk of what felt like tendon or something. It made an audible sound as a crunched into it. On top of that, the chicken tasted like cheap Costco frozen chicken. Flavor was just weird. I will say the service was very friendly and the environment was (mostly) nice. But also, there was a dab of some kind of sauce in my "clean" table and cold air was bleeding through the facade. And I hate blow dryers in the bathroom, but that's a nitpick.

Warning...this is not a Hawaiian plate lunch spot nor is it an authentic Japanese Grill.  It's a Chinese restaurant doing a lousy job of pretending to be these.  I'm from Hawaii and I can tell you that this place wouldn't stay open 3 months in the Islands.  Nobody in their right mind would support it. Totally fake but worst of all the food is awful.   I have pity on those diners who think they're eating 'Hawaiian' plate lunch.  Stay away!   And if you don't believe my review go check their Dept of Health grade. Been looking/waiting for a good Japanese/Hawaiian BBQ place and I'm so effing happy Makana opened. I've been three times already since its opening like a month ago. The sushi is excellent and all the meats are cooked perfectly. BBQ seafood mix is awesome with the chicken, shrimp, and Mahi mahi, and the BBQ short ribs and beef are super tender and delicious. Prices are reasonable and I plan to go through the entire menu. Loco Moco and the Katsu Burger look like they'd be awesome. Can't get enough of this place. Its got a nice ambiance too, definitely a good casual restaurant atmosphere for lunch/dinner with friends
